		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Dwedit wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">What about some kind of &quot;gun converter&quot; that connects to the controller port and the composite cable?  I think they had those things for Playstation 2.</div><br /><br />Playstation 1 and 2 have a lightgun called the Namco GunCon (and GunCon 2). These lightguns use a direct connection to the composite video signal to aid in their accuracy. The GunCon 2 particularly is quite an accurate lightgun. I have not used the original GunCon 1, only a clone which worked well but was more shakey than the GC2.<br /><br />Ofcourse it is still a lightgun, CRT required.

		

